WEBVTT

00:00.550 --> 00:03.320
The House Judiciary Committee
this week will begin its

00:03.320 --> 00:04.284
impeachment inquiry.

00:04.284 --> 00:05.870
First Daughter Stephanie McCord

00:05.890 --> 00:08.029
will testify today
in an open hearing,

00:08.060 --> 00:10.340
followed by First
Gentleman Henry McCord.

00:10.360 --> 00:12.302
Here to offer us an inside view

00:12.302 --> 00:14.986
is Capitol Hill
correspondent Priya Khatri.

00:15.031 --> 00:17.288
Priya, why is the House
investigation beginning

00:17.297 --> 00:18.800
with the president's family members?

00:18.826 --> 00:21.831
Normally, a president
would invoke executive privilege

00:21.831 --> 00:23.573
to protect anyone in her family

00:23.573 --> 00:25.650
or administration
from testifying, but...

00:25.680 --> 00:28.790
this is an unusual presidency
in many ways.

00:28.810 --> 00:31.333
Now, the president
has always maintained

00:31.342 --> 00:34.044
she had nothing to do with
the Iran government's hacking

00:34.044 --> 00:36.257
and leaking of
her opponent's private records

00:36.257 --> 00:37.660
during the campaign.

00:37.690 --> 00:40.462
But with the Senate
Intelligence Report broadening

00:40.462 --> 00:43.306
the investigation into
corruption and obstruction,

00:43.315 --> 00:46.675
these hearings can go
in any number of directions.

00:46.844 --> 00:48.640
Want to do some cardio with me?

00:48.670 --> 00:50.240
Get out of your head?

00:50.270 --> 00:53.410
I have to go over my WTO remarks.

00:53.440 --> 00:55.410
Did you get any sleep last night?

00:55.440 --> 00:57.180
A little.

00:57.210 --> 00:59.990
Kept thinking
about that first summer.

01:00.010 --> 01:02.320
Stevie at horse camp.

01:03.146 --> 01:05.019
Poor kiddo.

01:05.050 --> 01:06.906
So homesick.

01:07.050 --> 01:09.288
Why didn't I just let her come home?

01:09.324 --> 01:10.630
You said it would help her

01:10.650 --> 01:12.470
build character, and you were right.

01:12.951 --> 01:16.370
Are we crazy,
throwing her in with the sharks?

01:16.390 --> 01:18.737
Let's just hope Olivia's right

01:18.746 --> 01:20.840
and it's not a circus
like the Senate hearings.

01:20.860 --> 01:25.180
Just a House impeachment trial
on national television.

01:25.200 --> 01:27.210
We got nothing to fear.

01:27.240 --> 01:28.980
Except the sharks.

01:29.010 --> 01:31.720
Good thing we're all fast swimmers.

01:32.580 --> 01:33.830
Hmm.

01:36.050 --> 01:37.360
It is a kick-ass opening statement.

01:37.380 --> 01:39.244
And I'm not just saying that
'cause I did a pass on it.

01:39.280 --> 01:41.315
Yeah, well, let's hope it's enough

01:41.315 --> 01:43.920
to take campaign finance
violations off the table.

01:43.928 --> 01:45.662
If there's anything I can do

01:45.662 --> 01:48.071
to clear up
the Martha's Vineyard mishap...

01:48.080 --> 01:50.000
You say "mishap," I say "gift."

01:50.008 --> 01:51.288
The more they go after that mirage,

01:51.288 --> 01:52.924
the more we know they
don't have anything real.

01:52.933 --> 01:54.260
Well, let's not get cocky.

01:54.260 --> 01:55.404
Hanson may have given

01:55.404 --> 01:57.970
the House a bunch of
trumped-up charges to work with,

01:58.000 --> 02:00.275
but the House Chair
still has to litigate them all.

02:00.293 --> 02:02.062
Canning is a tough prosecutor and

02:02.062 --> 02:04.310
- he is not our friend.
- You'll forgive me

02:04.311 --> 02:06.110
if I'm confident I won't be convicted

02:06.115 --> 02:07.208
of murdering a state senator.

02:07.253 --> 02:10.044
Well, no, you put enough doubt
in the public's mind about it,

02:10.070 --> 02:12.450
- and we're all out of a job.
- With Heeney

02:12.480 --> 02:14.986
on the House Committee,
we've got a solid defender.

02:14.995 --> 02:16.690
And the markets are
a little wobbly this morning,

02:16.710 --> 02:18.290
but overall the economy's good.

02:18.320 --> 02:19.830
Your approval ratings are holding.

02:19.850 --> 02:21.706
Why are the markets wobbly?

02:21.742 --> 02:24.160
Eli Volk disappeared
during a trip to Moscow.

02:24.190 --> 02:26.470
The Technoflux IPO
was supposed to be Wednesday,

02:26.490 --> 02:28.600
- so it's got everyone rattled.
- As long as

02:28.630 --> 02:31.140
they find him in time to write
us another campaign cheque.

02:32.160 --> 02:33.870
What? Like no one else
was thinking that?

02:33.900 --> 02:35.084
No, just you.

02:35.146 --> 02:36.610
How does a...

02:36.630 --> 02:39.920
world-famous billionaire
just disappear?

02:39.946 --> 02:40.995
We'll be covering that

02:41.004 --> 02:43.180
- in your intelligence briefing.
- Knowing Volk,

02:43.210 --> 02:44.986
he was probably
on some peyote vision quest.

02:45.004 --> 02:48.590
I'm going to just grab something
I left in the office.

02:49.004 --> 02:50.711
Hey, Mum.

02:51.150 --> 02:55.030
That lady in charge on The
Great British Baking Show.

02:55.050 --> 02:56.060
Mary Berry?

02:56.090 --> 02:57.564
I have decided

02:57.591 --> 03:00.657
she's my ideal role model
for Leading While Female.

03:00.720 --> 03:01.537
Yes!

03:01.564 --> 03:04.737
Right? Always had a kind word,

03:04.746 --> 03:07.031
even when the technical
challenge was a disaster,

03:07.031 --> 03:08.010
and kept

03:08.030 --> 03:10.410
Paul Hollywood in line with a look.

03:10.440 --> 03:11.580
Impeccable blazers.

03:11.600 --> 03:12.968
She should run for office.

03:12.995 --> 03:15.680
No! We need her right where she is.

03:15.710 --> 03:18.120
Lot of Americans might say
the same about you.

03:18.140 --> 03:20.050
- So listen...
- I know.

03:20.080 --> 03:21.306
I'll be fine, Mum.

03:21.360 --> 03:23.591
This isn't horse camp, Stevie.

03:23.608 --> 03:25.590
If you don't want to do this...

03:25.620 --> 03:26.790
I got it.

03:26.820 --> 03:28.060
I'm ready.

03:28.090 --> 03:30.330
You're my brave girl, you know that?

03:30.350 --> 03:33.070
You, me and Mary Berry.

03:33.090 --> 03:34.500
See you after?

03:34.530 --> 03:36.540
You bet.

03:38.500 --> 03:40.248
Two days ago,

03:40.248 --> 03:44.810
Eli Volk, the aerospace engineer
and CEO of Technoflux,

03:44.840 --> 03:46.408
disappeared in Moscow

03:46.408 --> 03:49.413
while on tour to promote Technoflux's

03:49.413 --> 03:50.791
initial public offering.

03:50.800 --> 03:52.480
How do you disappear
in a surveillance state?

03:52.488 --> 03:56.862
He went to a private evening at
his friend's restaurant, and

03:56.897 --> 03:59.460
his security detail lost track of him.

03:59.480 --> 04:01.368
- Max?
- There's no evidence yet

04:01.368 --> 04:03.075
on any closed-circuit we can access,

04:03.075 --> 04:04.960
and no signals to any of his contacts.

04:04.968 --> 04:06.675
What are the working theories?

04:06.711 --> 04:08.053
Could be a mob hit,

04:08.088 --> 04:12.410
some rival corporation
trying to thwart the IPO,

04:12.430 --> 04:14.480
or it was state-ordered.

04:14.500 --> 04:16.221
We're working back channels

04:16.221 --> 04:17.528
to see if there's anything

04:17.536 --> 04:19.786
behind the Kremlin's public denials.

04:19.786 --> 04:21.803
- Sorry to interrupt.
Ma'am, it's time.  - Oh.

04:21.857 --> 04:22.568
The president would like

04:22.568 --> 04:25.128
to watch her daughter's
testimony before the House.

04:25.128 --> 04:27.662
We'll, review
the rest of the PDB privately.

04:27.671 --> 04:29.060
Thank you, everyone.

04:31.075 --> 04:33.324
Members of the Committee,

04:33.377 --> 04:36.930
we have before us charges
against a sitting president,

04:36.950 --> 04:40.530
members of her administration,
campaign staff and family,

04:40.560 --> 04:42.970
which, if shown to be true,

04:42.990 --> 04:46.510
pose a threat to the very heart
of our constitutional democracy.

04:46.530 --> 04:49.662
We are united as Americans
by our unwavering faith

04:49.662 --> 04:52.350
in the integrity of our elections.

04:52.370 --> 04:54.350
To thwart the voice of the people

04:54.370 --> 04:56.897
by manipulating
ill-gotten information

04:56.906 --> 05:00.720
provided by a foreign enemy is
an assault no one in this room,

05:00.750 --> 05:02.360
nay, this country,

05:02.380 --> 05:04.490
could or should ever tolerate.

05:04.520 --> 05:06.460
Ms McCord,

05:06.480 --> 05:08.488
not only is your
mother's reputation

05:08.480 --> 05:11.270
as an elected official
at stake here today,

05:11.290 --> 05:13.730
but the soul
of your country is as well.

05:13.760 --> 05:15.608
I would ask you to shine

05:15.600 --> 05:18.540
a clear and unwavering light
upon all that you know

05:18.560 --> 05:21.380
and stand before us today
as a citizen first.

05:21.840 --> 05:23.380
The chair now recognises

05:23.400 --> 05:24.817
ranking representative member Heeney

05:24.826 --> 05:25.626
for his opening statement.

05:25.626 --> 05:27.720
Let's see that right hook, Heeney.

05:28.337 --> 05:30.880
Good afternoon,
members of the Committee.

05:30.910 --> 05:32.942
Thank you for your testimony,
Ms McCord.

05:32.977 --> 05:34.350
We are here today to find out

05:34.355 --> 05:36.124
the truth, the truth of what happened

05:36.124 --> 05:38.933
between candidate McCord
and the government of Iran

05:38.942 --> 05:41.280
in the run-up
to the presidential election.

05:41.333 --> 05:43.230
We're also here to investigate

05:43.250 --> 05:46.088
all claims of obstruction of justice

05:46.097 --> 05:49.140
and campaign finance malfeasance.

05:49.160 --> 05:52.204
Ms McCord, you do understand
that it is your duty

05:52.213 --> 05:54.222
to answer all of our questions
to the very best

05:54.222 --> 05:56.204
- of your ability...
- Is he hungover?

05:56.204 --> 05:57.950
That's not good.

05:57.970 --> 05:59.822
Sorry to interrupt. I have INR.

05:59.820 --> 06:01.111
They said it's urgent.

06:01.128 --> 06:03.450
...thank you,
members of the Committee.

06:03.470 --> 06:04.915
...that the testimony
you're about to give

06:04.915 --> 06:06.120
is true and correct

06:06.140 --> 06:06.995
to the best of your knowledge,

06:07.004 --> 06:09.031
information and belief,
so help you God?

06:09.057 --> 06:10.915
- I do.
- INR just got a hit

06:10.915 --> 06:14.337
on Eli Volk in Moscow when
his phone briefly went live.

06:14.408 --> 06:15.386
And?

06:15.537 --> 06:18.710
Seems he's in the Iranian embassy.

06:20.380 --> 06:22.906
Iran captured Eli Volk?

06:22.977 --> 06:24.684
Looks like they're trying
to even the score

06:24.693 --> 06:26.773
for the capture
of Reza Mousavi in Lebanon.

06:26.808 --> 06:28.915
Iran already hacked a German bank

06:28.915 --> 06:30.693
and crashed an oil tanker.

06:30.693 --> 06:33.150
- The score was even.
- Well, not while

06:33.170 --> 06:35.950
we've got their Quds commander
in detention.

06:35.970 --> 06:37.790
How do you want to answer?

06:38.684 --> 06:40.755
Blake? First I want to find out

06:40.755 --> 06:42.888
how much Russia knew about this.

06:42.942 --> 06:45.590
I need President Salnikov
right away, please.

06:45.620 --> 06:46.791
Yes, ma'am.

06:48.560 --> 06:51.244
Well, at least the press can't
say I was colluding with Iran

06:51.244 --> 06:53.226
- on this one.
- Don't be so sure.

06:53.244 --> 06:57.240
Which means more headlines about
Iran at the worst possible time.

